blog.name: angelofberlin2000
blog.title: Like a Rose trampled on the ground
blog.description:
In addition to the pain and the exhaustion, he recalled how waiting on the cross between takes became tedious. To fight the boredom, he listened to music on headphones. One particular song called "Above All" (Like a Rose ...) by Michael W. Smith helped him through his most difficult moments.

"It arrived when I was confused and angry. I didn't think I could go on. The song described how Jesus was rejected and alone. That thought took me to a place — it opened an interior door that held me while on the cross," an emotional Caviezel explained. "The experience of feeling rejected and alone as all those around me laughed while drinking their hot coffees, oblivious to what was occurring. Jesus must have felt like this — forsaken, rejected, alone, and despised. It helped me pray in a very deep way — to pray without words, to pray from the heart. The discomfort, the loneliness, the split shoulder, the raw flesh all forced me into the arms of God because I had nowhere else to go for a performance I knew I was unable to create."
Jim Caviezel, Shamelessly Catholic

body:
Unwanted movie review.

I watched Constantine on @natashayess ’s insistance. Well not insistance, more like recommendation. XD I just don’t know how I feel about it. Didn’t think it would be about demons. I didn’t read the movie description. Shia Labeouf was a surprise as was Evie from the Mummy.

Some cool scene for sure. I’m just not the religious type so I couldn’t quite take it seriously. Tilda was a major surprise. Gorgeous and majestic as always. Loved the hair.

Hell was super extra with all the wind and fire. Lucifer made me uncomfortable in the way that he reminded me of the Joker. The rebelious demon spawn was disturbing in so many ways.

Keanu being quite douchey was unexpected. Holy water ampules, dragon’s breath and all the equipment gave me such video games vibes.

Idk what to say anymore. @natashayess has all the quotes. I wasn’t wowed by the movie. I don’t regret watching it though.

I’ve a long watchlist. Buckle up peeps.

body:
The Star/Asia News Network May 29, 2019

Keanu Reeves says he is a lonely guy

What does love mean to you?

You mean romantic love? You know, I’m the lonely guy. I don’t have anyone in my life. But if it does occur, I would respect and love the other person; hopefully it’ll happen for me.

Your fans are here and we love you so much, Keanu.
